My mum has been diagnosed with terminal cervical cancer secondary bone metastasis, that has now spread to her clavical and they are now suspecting the lungs too. so scared and worried as this has been going on for a while, shes in hospital now with a chest infection, a uti and kidney infection . her oxygen levels are low, and her usual stats, blood pressure etc is all low, but shes ok in herself - still joking smiling etc. shes being so brave - but can never tell if she is putting up a feont or not. 


	i have tried talking to the doctors there, but they dont really tell me everything , just literally the basics as to what shes had done while shes in as they are so busy. i dont know what to ask them or how to ask as everytime they are free they come to sit in the bay with my mum and i dont acyually want to ask them everthing in front.of my mum. 


	like how bad are things? (apart from the inevitable :,( ) 


	what am i to expect or look out for when that time comes? 


	heads a mess and dont even know if im supposed to put any of this on here but dont know where else to turn 




	tia.


	laura. x







#cancersucks# 


Reply














        Posted by
                  rily



	  	  18 Jul 2016 9:21 PM


Hello Ipcox1988. Sorry to hear about your Mum, and it is understandable how worried you are for her. We have a friendly group here for Carers Only . If you click the link and join the group, you should get help, advice and support from others looking after loved ones, and have experience of what you are going through. It may be an idea to copy and paste your above post in the group. Hope this helps. Best wishes.


