SOME ADVICE PLEASE ON ADVANCED PROSTATE CANCER








        Posted by
                  Yviemac



	  	  18 Jul 2016 11:30 AM


My husband is 57 and has advanced prostate cancer. First diagnosed nearly 8 years ago. He has undergone radiotherapy twice and chemo for 10 sessions. The cancer has now spread again and there is talk of perhaps Radium223 being used to assist. He had a recent admission to hospital as he had terrible back and hip pain. We are seeing the Oncologist tomorrow. He has had enzalutamide which hasn't worked effectively. Prior to that he was in a trial and had to come out of it.  Anyone out there with similar experience? It would be useful to know what treatments seem to work. 



Advanced prostate cancer 


Reply














        Posted by
                  Lakeslover



	  	  19 Jul 2016 9:14 AM


Hello Yviemac,




	Welcome to the community. I am sorry to hear about your husbands diagnosis.





	I recommend you join the prostate group here and post your question to the members of this group. I'm sure they will have experiences to share.









